display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex> is an uncurried form of the group morphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\rho \colon  G\to \mathop {\textrm {Aut}}\nolimits (K)]]></fr:tex>; i.e., it's a morphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \colon  G\times  K\to  K]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha (g,k)=\rho (g)(k)]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>Usually we write <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\cdot  k]]></fr:tex> instead of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha (g,k)]]></fr:tex> for the left action of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\in  G]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k\in  K]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
